The paper discusses the development of strategies for a natural language question answering system, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. This falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses decision making and probability estimation, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
